{
  "stem": "23645.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my brothers belonged to, one of them belonged to the Bund, which, of course, was to the left.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I mean, we had all these political organizations, but they were all Zionist organizations.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And most of them, except for the Bund, were advocating organizing-- you know, halutzim-- going to the state of Israel, going to Palestine, at the time.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Of course, we didn't refer to it as Israel at the time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I just wish that there was enough wisdom that they had done this, that more Jews would have left Poland before the madness occurred.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So when you speak about-- and then, of course, talk about going-- say, Rosh Hashanah, the welcoming of the new year.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "You know, the warmest memories that I have is standing beside my father in shul.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[SIGHING] [SOBBING] I didn't think that this would do this to me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And his tallis, he would-- and, you know, completely-- I was completely [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] hidden, you know, in in his tallis.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "How wonderfully secure I felt.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I hope I don't do this to you, Fran.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Take a moment.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a wonderful time of-- of being a child.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the security I felt, with this-- with this-- with this gesture of his, you know, and listening to the khazn sing, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] there's-- there's no words to describe that kind of a feeling, of having this.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, of course, the solemn time of Yom Kippur, of coming back after-- after the Kol Nidre, and the seriousness of it, and the feeling at home, afterwards.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And then the next day, Yom Kippur, my mother would bring a little bag.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she had fruit in there.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
